children.subject: In this semester (Fa 2017) they let us do the quizzes through the webcast. Although, towards the end of the class the prof got pretty annoyed that nobody was coming to lecture... so things could be different.

In Sprint 2017, EE16B was webcasted, but completing every in-lecture participation quiz gives you a second homework drop.  About conflicting final exams, it's up to the instructor and you should email her/him.  In my past experience, signing up for conflicting courses is not a reason instructors like to allow for taking an alternate final.

history.content: I know that EE16B has been webcasted for the past few semesters, but what about alternative midterms and final? I have time conflict with EE126. Thanks!
